unittitle_ssm: Alumni Scrapbook and Alumni Association Minutes
abstract_ssm: This collection consists primarily of the earliest minutes, correspondence and records of the Alumni Association of New York University (then, the University of the City of New York). This collection is divided into two series. Series I consists of the The Alumni Association Scrapbook and dates from 1846 to 1856. This series was compiled by William R. Martin, secretary of the Association, in 1886. Series II consists of the Alumni Association Minutes and dates from 1834 to 1934. This series is arranged chronologically.
